FBIS4-37120 "drnes117_u_94002" FBIS-NES-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 Nepal Opposition Party Splits Into Two Factions Opposition Party Splits Into Two Factions BK1706070294 Hong Kong AFP in English 1426 GMT 16 Jun 94 BK1706070294 Hong Kong AFP English BFN [Text] Kathmandu, June 16 (AFP) -- Nepal's second largest parliamentary opposition party, the United Peoples Front (UPF), has split into two factions after a party official was expelled from a UPF committee, a party source said Thursday. Six of the party's MPs pushed out UPF convenor Baburam Bhattarai from the committee he headed for using the party for personal gain, the source said. The two new UPF factions have filed petitions to the Chief Election Commission Office seeking exclusive recognition for the next general elections in 1996.
